WEBVTT

00:00.734 --> 00:02.266
<i>Previously on</i>
Two and a Half Men...

00:02.291 --> 00:03.777
I am determined to find

00:03.877 --> 00:05.154
someone who wants
to be with me

00:05.155 --> 00:07.398
for who I am, not what I have.

00:07.644 --> 00:09.493
My point is you can be whoever
you want to be.

00:09.781 --> 00:10.896
I can help you out with that.

00:10.898 --> 00:13.182
I appreciate it... Kate.

00:13.184 --> 00:14.233
Sam Wilson.

00:14.235 --> 00:16.184
Maybe you could crash here.

00:16.187 --> 00:17.236
Have you really
thought this through?

00:17.238 --> 00:19.538
I got to see
where this goes with Kate.

00:19.540 --> 00:20.790
I think it is great

00:20.792 --> 00:22.875
that you're working on
your computer stuff,

00:22.877 --> 00:24.526
but we need help now.

00:24.528 --> 00:25.544
Say no more.

00:25.546 --> 00:27.746
I'll start looking
for a job.

00:32.418 --> 00:33.702
Hey.

00:33.704 --> 00:36.972
Oh, look who finally
decided to show up.

00:36.974 --> 00:38.874
Uh, yeah, I got
stuck in traffic.

00:38.876 --> 00:39.975
Traffic, pfft.

00:39.977 --> 00:42.645
You were with <i>her,</i>
weren't you?

00:42.647 --> 00:45.014
Really, Alan?

00:45.016 --> 00:46.849
Well, I don't mean to sound
like a broken record,

00:46.851 --> 00:48.067
but you're never
home anymore.

00:48.069 --> 00:49.602
I was just there
the other night.

00:49.604 --> 00:50.903
And all you did
was watch the game

00:50.905 --> 00:52.938
and fall asleep.
Remember how we used

00:52.940 --> 00:55.224
to stay up all night
and just talk?

00:55.226 --> 00:57.993
Okay, you know, fine,
we can talk now.

00:57.995 --> 00:58.944
What's on your mind?

00:58.946 --> 01:00.395
Nothing. I'm fine.

01:00.397 --> 01:03.899
I'm not
a mind reader, Alan.

01:03.901 --> 01:06.836
Well, not that
you care, but...

01:06.838 --> 01:08.621
I'm rattling around
in that big house

01:08.623 --> 01:09.622
all by myself.

01:09.624 --> 01:12.958
I miss you.
There, I said it.

01:12.960 --> 01:14.210
I miss you, too.

01:14.212 --> 01:16.411
Well, you got a funny
way of showing it.

01:16.413 --> 01:18.848
You do understand I have
a girlfriend, right?

01:18.850 --> 01:19.748
So do I.

01:19.750 --> 01:21.684
A-Another peach
mojito, please.

01:21.686 --> 01:23.886
What are you drinking?
It's on me.

01:23.888 --> 01:25.387
And by "on me,"
I mean the money

01:25.389 --> 01:26.805
you left me to
pay the bills,

01:26.807 --> 01:28.357
which, incidentally,
I used for other stuff,

01:28.359 --> 01:30.259
so I'll need money
to pay the bills.

01:32.479 --> 01:34.196
I'll have
a ginger ale, please.

01:34.198 --> 01:35.481
Ginger ale?

01:35.483 --> 01:37.483
Yeah, my stomach's
been bothering me.

01:37.485 --> 01:39.268
I haven't really been
feeling myself lately.

01:39.270 --> 01:40.435
Which self would
that be?

01:40.437 --> 01:42.104
Walden Schmidt
or Sam Wilson?

01:42.106 --> 01:44.990
Sam Wilson has
a lot of stress.

01:44.992 --> 01:46.375
Thank you.

01:46.377 --> 01:47.459
Money's tight.

01:47.461 --> 01:49.611
You'd be surprised
what that does to a guy.

01:49.613 --> 01:51.163
Please, I've been so
desperate for money,

01:51.165 --> 01:52.831
I've climbed into
fountains at night

01:52.833 --> 01:55.467
and stolen the
wishes of children.

01:55.469 --> 01:57.136
So you get it.

01:57.138 --> 01:58.420
What I don't get
is why you don't

01:58.422 --> 02:00.306
resolve the stress and just
tell Kate the truth.

02:00.308 --> 02:01.590
That's not gonna happen.

02:01.592 --> 02:02.641
Why not?
I don't know,

02:02.643 --> 02:04.293
everything's
going so great,

02:04.295 --> 02:05.811
I don't want
to screw it up.

02:05.813 --> 02:08.681
Oh, that's not good.

02:09.549 --> 02:12.222
♪ Men, men, men, men,
manly men, men, men ♪

02:12.247 --> 02:12.838
♪ Ah...
♪ Men.

02:12.839 --> 02:16.839
<font color="#00FF00">♪ Two and a Half Men 10x12 ♪</font>
<font color="#00FFFF">Welcome to Alancrest</font>
