02:21.910 --> 02:23.360
♪ <i>Men.</i> ♪

02:24.160 --> 02:26.244
I don't know whether this is
beef or chicken,

02:26.246 --> 02:28.496
but it's definitely
worth 79 cents.

02:31.883 --> 02:33.167
What's the matter?

02:33.169 --> 02:36.704
My life has been
a complete waste of time.

02:36.706 --> 02:39.423
Otherwise, I'm terrific.

02:39.425 --> 02:40.791
Whoa, whoa, whoa.

02:40.793 --> 02:43.077
Wait, is this...
is this one of

02:43.079 --> 02:44.328
the dresses you made?
Mm-hmm.

02:44.330 --> 02:46.013
Why are you throwing it away?

02:46.015 --> 02:48.933
Because, apparently...
my stuff's not good enough

02:48.935 --> 02:51.519
to get a job
that pays nothing.

02:51.521 --> 02:53.521
You didn't get the internship?

02:53.523 --> 02:56.974
Nope. Rejected by the guy
who assists the guy

02:56.976 --> 03:00.111
who assists the guy
who designs Snooki's

03:00.113 --> 03:03.531
signature line
of baby thongs.

03:03.533 --> 03:06.016
Okay, don't worry,
you're gonna get next one.

03:06.018 --> 03:08.619
There is no next one.

03:08.621 --> 03:10.488
I mean, obviously

03:10.490 --> 03:12.690
I don't have what it takes
to be a fashion designer.

03:12.692 --> 03:15.126
And at a certain point,
I just have to bite the bullet

03:15.128 --> 03:16.877
and admit it is not happening.

03:16.879 --> 03:18.579
But you're not at that point.

03:18.581 --> 03:20.047
Three words:

03:20.049 --> 03:21.532
Snooki's...

03:21.534 --> 03:22.866
baby...

03:22.868 --> 03:24.919
thongs!

03:24.921 --> 03:27.037
I think your designs are great.

03:27.039 --> 03:29.423
You have to say that;
I have sex with you.

03:30.692 --> 03:32.059
True.

03:32.061 --> 03:36.230
But if I was a woman,
I would totally wear this dress.

03:37.182 --> 03:38.549
Hell, three shots of tequila

03:38.551 --> 03:40.067
and I would wear this dress.

03:40.885 --> 03:42.987
And I would work it!

03:42.989 --> 03:45.723
Okay, don't make me laugh
when I'm trying to cry.

03:45.725 --> 03:47.525
Too late, because
I am fierce.

03:52.664 --> 03:54.064
I love you, Sam.

03:54.066 --> 03:56.901
Uh, you have to say that;
I have sex with you.

03:56.903 --> 03:59.253
Okay, the real test is,

03:59.255 --> 04:01.739
will you have sex with me
wearing that dress?

04:01.741 --> 04:05.426
You get the tequila,
I'll go put on some heels.

04:09.131 --> 04:11.265
Lightly salted,
just the way you like.

04:11.267 --> 04:13.050
Mm, thanks.

04:13.052 --> 04:14.969
Who could've seen
this coming?

04:14.971 --> 04:15.936
Right.

04:15.938 --> 04:17.721
We end up with the house.

04:17.724 --> 04:20.190
Unbelievable.

04:20.192 --> 04:21.726
You know how
I used to say

04:21.728 --> 04:23.694
you'd have to pay me
to hang out with you?

04:23.696 --> 04:24.695
Yeah.

04:24.697 --> 04:26.864
Here we are!

04:27.733 --> 04:28.983
Hey, guys.

04:28.985 --> 04:30.100
Mm.!

04:30.102 --> 04:32.069
Oh, Look who it is.
Sam Wilson.

04:32.071 --> 04:33.204
Hey, Alan,

04:33.206 --> 04:34.622
can I, can I talk to you
for a second?

04:34.624 --> 04:35.606
Oh, sure.

04:35.608 --> 04:37.908
The principal wants to see me.
Mm.

04:39.211 --> 04:41.962
Oh, uh, Berta,
I brought some laundry by.

04:41.964 --> 04:43.297
Uh, do you mind?

04:43.299 --> 04:46.000
It's your machine.
Knock yourself out.

04:49.504 --> 04:51.272
So, what's up?

04:51.274 --> 04:54.141
I'm transferring $100,000
into your bank account.

04:54.143 --> 04:57.061
A hundred... thousand...

04:57.063 --> 04:58.345
Catch me, Lord.

04:59.399 --> 05:00.481
Uh-oh, uh-oh.

05:00.483 --> 05:01.899
I-I think I need
to sit down.

05:01.901 --> 05:03.250
Yeah, yeah.
I...

05:03.252 --> 05:05.302
I-I could swear
that I heard you say

05:05.304 --> 05:07.321
you were gonna put
$100,000 into my account.

05:07.323 --> 05:08.355
I am.

05:08.357 --> 05:10.524
There it goes again.

05:10.526 --> 05:12.610
It's-it's like the teacups
at Disneyland.

05:12.612 --> 05:15.246
How can I ever thank you?

05:15.248 --> 05:17.147
The money's not for you,
it's for Kate.

05:17.149 --> 05:18.999
Next time, lead with that.

05:19.001 --> 05:21.001
I want you to invest
in her fashion designs.

05:21.003 --> 05:23.003
What?
She's really talented,

05:23.005 --> 05:24.655
but nobody will
give her a shot.

05:24.657 --> 05:26.323
Are you sure she's talented?

05:26.325 --> 05:27.991
It isn't just
boom-shaka-laka-laka,

05:27.993 --> 05:29.710
boom-shaka-laka-laka?

05:30.695 --> 05:32.996
I'm about to give you
a boom-shaka-laka.

05:34.499 --> 05:37.268
No, $100,000 will help
her start her company.

05:37.270 --> 05:39.186
So give it to her.
I can't.

05:39.188 --> 05:40.688
I'm Sam Wilson.
I'm broke.

05:40.690 --> 05:42.840
But you can,
because you're

05:42.842 --> 05:44.642
Alan Harper,
billionaire.

05:44.644 --> 05:46.844
Oh...

05:48.697 --> 05:51.482
Fashion's kind of risky.

05:52.834 --> 05:54.985
And Alan Harper did not
become a billionaire

05:54.987 --> 05:57.004
by taking unnecessary risks.

05:57.006 --> 06:00.357
You are taking an
unnecessary risk right now.

06:00.359 --> 06:03.127
No, I-I'm just saying that I'd
rather put my money into gold,

06:03.129 --> 06:04.578
or maybe start a vineyard.

06:04.580 --> 06:06.029
Alancrest.

06:06.031 --> 06:09.383
You know, fine, when
you make $100,000--

06:09.385 --> 06:11.085
I don't even have
to finish that.

06:11.087 --> 06:14.922
I-I want <i>my</i> money
invested in Kate.

06:14.924 --> 06:17.007
Okay, no problem.

06:17.009 --> 06:19.977
But I'll have to see
some of her sketches first.

06:19.979 --> 06:20.339
Alan.

06:20.364 --> 06:22.290
What? You want this to be
believable, don't you?

06:22.765 --> 06:24.031
Okay, fine.

06:24.033 --> 06:25.399
Have us over
tomorrow night.

06:25.401 --> 06:27.101
Ooh, kind of short notice.

06:27.103 --> 06:28.435
Alan!

06:28.437 --> 06:29.737
Can't we do this at your house?

06:29.739 --> 06:32.940
This is my house!

06:35.827 --> 06:39.897
Awfully rude for a guy
who wants my money.

06:41.000 --> 06:47.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

06:51.126 --> 06:54.445
It's like you've never
washed a dish in your life.

06:54.447 --> 06:56.514
What are you
talking about?

06:56.516 --> 06:58.966
There's still SpaghettiOs
on this plate.

07:00.686 --> 07:03.053
Well, you're the one
that wanted to be all fancy

07:03.055 --> 07:05.940
and said we couldn't eat them
straight out of the can.

07:06.858 --> 07:07.975
Ugh.

07:07.977 --> 07:11.028
Oh, speaking of fancy,
I saw Alan today.

07:11.030 --> 07:12.730
Ew.

07:12.732 --> 07:15.616
It was actually a really
interesting conversation.

07:15.618 --> 07:18.035
He's looking for some
new investments.

07:18.037 --> 07:21.288
He should go and buy himself
a better personality.

07:21.290 --> 07:23.157
Nobody's that rich.

07:23.159 --> 07:26.243
Uh, but I did tell him
that you're trying to start

07:26.245 --> 07:27.778
your own fashion company.

07:27.780 --> 07:29.446
Oh, Sam, you didn't.

07:29.448 --> 07:31.081
Oh, but I did.

07:32.117 --> 07:33.801
Well, he's in a position
to help you.

07:33.803 --> 07:35.252
I don't want his help.

07:35.254 --> 07:37.004
Unless I'm gonna start
a line called

07:37.006 --> 07:39.340
House of Douche.

07:39.342 --> 07:40.641
Don't be ridiculous.

07:40.643 --> 07:42.960
I'm sure that name's
already taken.

07:42.962 --> 07:45.980
Hey, he could be the answer
to all your problems.

07:45.982 --> 07:47.297
Oh, I don't know.

07:47.299 --> 07:48.515
Before you say no,

07:48.517 --> 07:50.184
he invited us over
tomorrow night

07:50.186 --> 07:52.186
so you can show him
your designs.

07:53.104 --> 07:55.689
Really think he'd invest in me?

07:55.691 --> 07:57.358
He'd have to be an idiot not to.

07:57.360 --> 07:58.993
But he is an idiot.

07:58.995 --> 08:01.645
True.

08:02.697 --> 08:04.114
Give it a chance?

08:04.116 --> 08:05.482
All right.

08:05.484 --> 08:06.667
I'll do it.

08:06.669 --> 08:09.203
Great. Oh, did I mention
that if you take his money,

08:09.205 --> 08:10.704
you have to
sleep with him?

08:12.758 --> 08:15.175
I'm kidding;
I'll totally do him.

08:25.503 --> 08:27.137
Ah! Sam, Kate.

08:27.139 --> 08:28.672
Welcome to Alancrest.

08:28.674 --> 08:31.058
W-Why are you
wearing pajamas?

08:31.060 --> 08:32.693
I'm rich. I can.

08:32.695 --> 08:35.229
Mm. You have
a beautiful home.

08:35.231 --> 08:37.014
It'll work
until my castle's finished.

08:37.015 --> 08:39.533
<i>Entrez-vous.</i>

08:39.534 --> 08:42.035
Uh, that's French for
"enter, you."

08:42.038 --> 08:43.504
Oh, look,

08:43.506 --> 08:45.239
my panoramic ocean view.

08:45.241 --> 08:47.574
You can follow my
seagulls on Twitter.

08:48.710 --> 08:50.744
Hashtag, "Gulls gone wild."

08:51.997 --> 08:53.196
Oh, ah, delightful!

08:53.198 --> 08:55.582
Thank you, Berta.
That will be all.

08:55.584 --> 08:57.718
Damn right it will!

08:57.720 --> 09:00.370
She's been
with the family for years.

09:00.372 --> 09:02.089
They say you're not really rich

09:02.091 --> 09:04.207
until you have servants
who hate you.

09:04.209 --> 09:07.311
Uh, Alan, Kate brought
her portfolio to show you.

09:07.313 --> 09:08.595
Oh, yes!

09:08.597 --> 09:10.147
Kate, please
take a seat.

09:10.149 --> 09:11.598
Take my breath away!

09:11.600 --> 09:13.767
Oh, I'd love to.

09:13.769 --> 09:16.904
I made some new sketches
just for you.

09:16.906 --> 09:18.739
Uh, yeah, she's been
working really hard on them.

09:18.741 --> 09:20.774
I-I think you're really
gonna like what you see.

09:20.776 --> 09:21.742
No offense, Sam,

09:21.744 --> 09:23.944
but look at the
way <i>you</i> dress.

09:24.829 --> 09:26.530
Mm.

09:26.532 --> 09:27.831
All right.

09:27.833 --> 09:29.950
Oh, it's-it's nice.

09:29.952 --> 09:31.669
No, I-I like
what you did here.

09:31.671 --> 09:32.736
Thank you.

09:33.705 --> 09:35.506
Uh, cap sleeves are
last season, but,

09:35.508 --> 09:37.741
you know, okay.

09:38.576 --> 09:40.010
Oh, you know,
I'm kind of done

09:40.012 --> 09:42.092
with rompers, but I understand
what you're going for.

09:43.081 --> 09:44.348
Oh, oh.

09:44.350 --> 09:45.683
Velvet.

09:45.685 --> 09:47.101
Kind of whorish.

09:47.103 --> 09:49.636
- Excuse me?
- Okay.

09:49.638 --> 09:52.473
You know what, uh, Kate,
why don't you run out to the car

09:52.475 --> 09:53.724
and grab some of your samples.

09:53.726 --> 09:55.893
I think Alan would
love to see them.

09:55.895 --> 09:57.444
Yeah, sure.

09:57.446 --> 10:00.064
Just hope
they're not too whorish.

10:00.066 --> 10:01.098
Yeah.

10:01.100 --> 10:03.233
Let's leave that
to Lady Gaga.

10:05.286 --> 10:06.904
Ow!

10:08.039 --> 10:09.957
What the hell
is the matter with you?

10:09.959 --> 10:12.376
Me? She's the one
who paired an empire waist

10:12.378 --> 10:14.461
with a Peter Pan collar!

10:14.463 --> 10:19.383
You're supposed to be a simple
rich guy, not a gay Bruce Wayne.

10:19.385 --> 10:22.386
Hey, hey, you have
your character, I have mine.

10:22.388 --> 10:25.139
Well, your character is a
festering heap of human waste!

10:25.141 --> 10:28.008
I think we both know, if I had
money, I'd be the biggest

10:28.010 --> 10:31.428
festering heap of human waste
that ever lived!

10:31.430 --> 10:34.314
All you have to do is tell her
that you want to invest

10:34.316 --> 10:36.100
and give her my $100,000.

10:36.102 --> 10:39.403
Well, fine,
but velvet is whorish.

10:39.405 --> 10:41.021
Okay, here we are.

10:41.023 --> 10:43.690
Uh, let's see.

10:43.692 --> 10:45.809
This is a cute, little shift

10:45.811 --> 10:47.778
that goes from
day to night.

10:47.780 --> 10:49.780
I love them all!
What?

10:49.782 --> 10:51.165
You-you haven't even seen them.

10:51.167 --> 10:53.500
I've seen all I
need to see, Kate.

10:53.502 --> 10:55.836
I want to invest in
your line of clothing.

10:55.838 --> 10:56.620
Really?

10:56.622 --> 10:57.621
Yes! Now tell me,

10:57.623 --> 10:58.672
what's our
business plan?

10:58.674 --> 11:00.174
Well, it depends.
If I had enough money,

11:00.176 --> 11:02.009
I'd put a show together for
Fashion Week in New York.

11:02.011 --> 11:03.093
That way, I'd be able to...

11:03.095 --> 11:05.829
Sounds great. Pack
your bags for New York,

11:05.831 --> 11:10.500
because I'm gonna write
you a check for $50,000.

11:10.502 --> 11:12.519
What?!

11:12.521 --> 11:13.887
Sam, did you hear that?

11:13.889 --> 11:15.305
Uh, yeah, I did.

11:15.307 --> 11:16.840
What's the-- $50,000?

11:16.842 --> 11:18.192
I-I know it's a lot.

11:18.194 --> 11:20.844
But I believe in her, and
I want to take a chance.

11:20.846 --> 11:22.112
Uh, well,

11:22.114 --> 11:23.814
if you really believe
in her, maybe you'd...

11:23.816 --> 11:25.732
maybe you'd like to invest
a little bit more.

11:25.734 --> 11:26.349
Sam.

11:26.351 --> 11:27.484
No, no, no.

11:27.486 --> 11:29.620
He's right.

11:29.622 --> 11:32.072
I'm gonna hate
myself for this.

11:32.074 --> 11:34.458
But what the heck.

11:34.460 --> 11:38.045
$60,000.

11:44.535 --> 11:48.472
I can't believe Alan
gave me $100,000.

11:48.474 --> 11:52.092
I can't believe
it took him two hours to do it.

11:52.094 --> 11:54.428
Thank you.

11:54.430 --> 11:56.880
What are you thanking me for?

11:56.882 --> 11:59.933
Because I know none of this
would've happened without you.

11:59.935 --> 12:01.935
I just introduced you.

12:01.937 --> 12:04.321
Your whorish velvet
did the rest.

12:07.243 --> 12:09.243
You are the sweetest...

12:09.245 --> 12:11.912
most generous...

12:11.914 --> 12:14.281
open, giving...

12:14.283 --> 12:17.034
caring, genuine person
I've ever met, Sam Wilson.

12:17.036 --> 12:19.786
That's me.

12:19.788 --> 12:23.340
Good old Sam Wilson.

12:23.342 --> 12:26.126
This whole thing...
is incredible.

12:26.128 --> 12:27.577
I am so excited.

12:27.579 --> 12:29.346
Me, too.

12:29.348 --> 12:32.349
Are you sure?

12:32.351 --> 12:33.717
What do you mean?

12:33.719 --> 12:35.719
Well, it just
seems like, um,

12:35.721 --> 12:38.689
Little Sam doesn't have
his head in the game.

12:38.691 --> 12:41.275
Um...

12:41.277 --> 12:43.277
